    },
    {
      "id": "1481032427949527262",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-10T20:54:07.075+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Sure, sounds good!\n\n> It would be useful to have a number of different configurations, such as synchronous/asynchronous and different widths and depths.\n\nI would suggest initially adding 6 configurations taped out during Run 1 to this PDK repo. The exact configurations can be found in the compiler repo releases. These ones will be the first to be verified in silicon (successfully I hope \ud83d\ude04), so it makes sense to use them in most cases.",
      "author": {
        "id": "709384666909507634",
        "name": "egorxe",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Egor Lukyanchenko",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-03_media/3-FB033.png"
      },
      "attachments": [],
      "embeds": [],
      "stickers": [],
      "reactions": [],
      "mentions": [],
